🧠Interested by alternatives to backprop? 📈...scaling them to challenging tasks? 🧮...their theory, and the new avenues they open for ML? 🔥...the design of #BeyondBackpropagation hardware? ➡️Well, with @LightOnIO & friends we have a frenzy of #NeurIPS2020 papers for you! https://t.co/alnmqC4QfK

🎉First, we have a #NeurIPS2020 paper on scaling an alternative to backpropagation to hard tasks. 📈At variance with previous beliefs, we show that Direct Feedback Alignment *can* scale to challenging tasks and modern architectures, up to Transformers! 🔗https://t.co/SQeU6xI84e https://t.co/ZHexWmCJeZ

🤔But why are alternatives to backpropagation so exciting? 🦾In an oral at the #NeurIPS2020 #BeyondBackpropagation workshop, we show that they open new avenues for dedicated ML hardware, especially for extreme-scale models. Don't like the hardware lottery? Well, just rig it! https://t.co/40TL7eCmn2

🤯But wait, there is more! 🛡️Again at #NeurIPS2020 #BeyondBackpropagation workshop, we introduce a new class of defence against adversarial attacks based on *parameters obfuscation* using a @LightOnIO photonic co-processor. Here, ignorance truly is bliss. https://t.co/2eHiwzXFyF

🙋All of this leaving you wondering *how* exactly Direct Feedback Alignment works? 🧑‍🏫Check-out Maria Refinetti, @stephanedascoli, @oharub, and @sdgoldt work at the #NeurIPS2020 #BeyondBackpropagation workshop on cracking the learning dynamics of DFA. 🔗https://t.co/DIHIOZMA4I https://t.co/97qUO595uR

Occurs to me that a potential variant on data augmentation for image data could be achieved by additive features, if you have image of cat add a mouse, if you have image of garage add a car, etc. for labeled data this should be reasonable. Just brainstorming. #NeurIPS2020

The keynote talk by @isbellHFh on algorithmic bias at #NeurIPS2020 is UNBELIEVABLE. I don't want to spoil too much, but it's clear many hours went into creating this keynote based on A Christmas Carol, complete with @mlittmancs as Scrooge. https://t.co/eG52v12aBq
A way to think about the meaning of self-supervised learning is that it uses the machinery of supervised learning but where labels are not human generated. #NeurIPS2020

Just like NLP models mask a word and predict replacement as a form of self-supervised prettaining, I don’t see why a generative model can’t be trained in a similar fashion for images with masked partitions. Just brainstorming. #NeurIPS2020

Notable breakthrough in GANs training presented by @NVIDIAAI at #NeurIPS2020. The authors propose an adaptive discriminator augmentation to stabilize training on limited data without any change in the loss function or network architecture. Catching up with #NeurIPS2020; here's one takeaway from Chris Bishop's keynote: their holographic storage uses ML to restore bits from hologram, but the data is encrypted first. ML only operates on encrypted (basically random!) bits, so synthetic training data is as good as any.
